libfov
------------------------------------------
libfov is a C library for calculating fields of view and lighting on low
resolution rasters, suitable for roguelike games. In that screenshot below,
imagine that green dot is your character in a computer game, and as you walk
around (move between tiles on the grid), you want to know which tiles you can
see and which tiles you cannot. libfov calculates exactly that.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.7-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-9-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.10.2-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://code.google.com/p/libfov/

Canonical download:
  http://libfov.googlecode.com/files/libfov-1.0.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libfov-1.0.4-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libfov-1.0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libfov-1.0.4-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libfov-1.0.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libfov1-1.0.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libfov-devel-1.0.4-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libfov)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libfov.README
  /usr/share/doc/libfov/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libfov/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libfov/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libfov/README

(libfov1)
  /usr/bin/cygfov-1.dll

(libfov-devel)
  /usr/include/fov/fov.h
  /usr/lib/fov/include/config.h
  /usr/lib/libfov.a
  /usr/lib/libfov.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libfov.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libfov.pc

